{4020}{}{With drugs like that, it sounds like you're manufacturing chems, not just medicine.}
{4030}{}{Thanks Doctor, I'll go see him.}
{5000}{}{(He looks at you with begrudging respect) Nice catch. You're smarter than you look.}
{5010}{}{Nice try, Doc. This is gonna cost you.}
{5020}{}{Forget it, I don't want to get involved.}
{6000}{}{(His face hardens) I assumed as much. Unfortunately for you, I don't have any money. The only thing I've got are healing supplies. But they're meant for people who actually need them, you grasping little shit.}
{6010}{}{I'll take 'em. Thanks, Doc. You have my silence. Well, probably.}
{6020}{}{Forget it. Keep them. Goodbye.}
{7000}{}{I'm the town doctor. People get injured, sick, I patch 'em up best I can. There's not much I can do these days. The Captain's stranglehold on trade's stopping most caravans from bothering with us. No trade means no medicine.}
{7010}{}{That sounds bad. Anything I can do to help?}
{7020}{}{I had something else I wanted to ask you.}
{8000}{}{Hmm, well I'm always on the lookout for broc flower and xander root. Get me enough, I'll whip you up a batch of healing powder. As well as keep the leftovers for the hospital, of course.}
{8010}{}{Deal. I'll bring some by later. I had some other questions.}
{8020}{}{I'll go look for some now, thanks.}
{9000}{}{Get out of my sight.@@Get lost, you little shit.@@::spits::@@Get out of my hospital!}
{10000}{}{Sweet Jesus, you're hideous.@@Please, leave me to my work.@@I'm sorry, please, you're upsetting the other patients.}
{11000}{}{Wish I could help you. Sorry, supplies are limited and we've got to prioritise the people who need it the most.}
{11010}{}{You're low on supplies? Anything I could help with?}
{11020}{}{That's too bad, could I ask you something else?}
{11030}{}{What a shame. Goodbye.}
